### Export OpenTelemetry Environment Variables for New Relic

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/documentation/nextjs/faqs/cloud-providers.md

These environment variables configure the OpenTelemetry SDK to send data to New Relic. Key variables include the service name, endpoint, and New Relic ingest license key. Ensure `<your_license_key>` is replaced with your actual key.

```sh
export OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=nextjs-otel-app
export OTEL_RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTES=service.instance.id=123
export OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=https://otlp.nr-data.net
export OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_HEADERS=api-key=<your_license_key>
export OTEL_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE_LENGTH_LIMIT=4095
export OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_COMPRESSION=gzip
export OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_PROTOCOL=http/protobuf
export OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_METRICS_TEMPORALITY_PREFERENCE=delta
```

